Mental day of surfing. Such a close heat today five minutes left and I knew I needed a 8.45 I was a little nervous and then told myself to stay calm. I still have time. Somehow this wave came right to me, and I was so nervous, but I just thought to myself that it's all or nothing. Somehow the wave ended up an 8.0 just short of the score i needed and ended up getting another wave to secure the score. Super stoked to have make it to the quarterfinals. Good job to all the other surfers. Everyone was ripping this whole event. Looking forward to keep the ball rolling into the quarterfinals. Also  thank you everybody for watching and all the kind messages we will be on tomorrow.
@riordanpringle 🎥💯

Super tough loss for me in the quarterfinals, but that's OK I'm super proud of myself and my surfing. I made a few mistakes and that cost me the heat, but that is contests can't win them all. For now i hold my head high and come back even stronger next year. Thank you so much. @wsl.qs for the event and looking forward for next year. Mahalo to all the locals for letting us surf your special wave. And the Tahitian brothers for always helping us when we are here in paradise. 💯❤️🙏🏼

Learning to enjoy the process. Life is not meant to be rushed, but meant to be enjoyed for every moment and second we have on this earth is not promised. Time flys and life keeps on going even with out us. Im gonna enjoy the ride And continue to strive to better myself every day. That's what life is all about 💯🙏🏼🥷🏻 @through.the.doggy.door

💔💔💔💔 I can't really put into words the feeling I am feeling at the moment. I just want to put it out there for people that didn't really know Ronson. Ronson was one of the most respectful, nicest loving person you could ever meet. He would give you the shirt off of his back if you needed it but also he was one of the toughest kids I ever met and let me tell you he would let you know that right away. Ronson took me in when I was a little kid living on the beach with my parents. I didnt have much to eat and he would always bring me to his house to feed me and treat me as if I was his little brother. Growing up on the west side was tough, but having a big brother like Ronson protecting me all the time was priceless. I never will forget the awesome times we had and also hard times we have gone through together. I will never forget all the awesome surf sessions and amazing times with you my brother. Life is really short and we should all show a little more love and respect like Ronson did. I love you brother. Until we meet again. Also if any of my family or friends are going through anything, please let people know. We all go through hard times. It's good to have some people around you making you feel like you are wanted. Call your loved ones and tell them you care for them. Life is too short. I'm really happy I got to hear your voice on the phone yesterday my brother, 💔

Got together and went to our spot that we all used to play at when we were kids. One of Ronson's favorite spots. We all used to come here when we were little and play on the reef when there was no waves cuz we were so anxious to surf. Knowing that you wont be here physically is tough but I know you'll always be with us in our hearts. I was truly blessed to have you as a friend in this life. Gone way too soon. Until we meet again. I love you Ronson Silva 💔💔💔 MAKAHA BOYS FOR LIFE 💯

It's a story about a human, Who has fought through adversity and difficult times and never gave up on his dreams. This can be a inspiration for anyone in the world for whatever it is you love believe or dream in doing anything is possible @through.the.doggy.door it's just the beginning of my story. Three months and two days sober today. I can definitely say I do not miss anything to do with drinking alcohol. Loosing one of my best friends  along the way definitely made me realize how precious and quickly a life can be gone.  drugs, and alcohol is not the way. Super proud of myself for being strong and can't wait to keep it going. It ain't a easy task, but believing in yourself and knowing that you can do it is always the best thing to do. U have to be strong and never give up. Super thankful for my girlfriend, family and all my friends for being there for me as well and also my wonderful sponsors who support me in and out the water.❤️🙏🏼 #threemonthsnoalcohol #BLESSED
